net.markenwerk.commons.collections.sequences

Class AbstractSequence<Payload>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.markenwerk.commons.collections.sources.AbstractSource<Payload>
      • net.markenwerk.commons.collections.sources.AbstractIndexedSource<Payload>
        • net.markenwerk.commons.collections.sequences.AbstractSequence<Payload>
  • Type Parameters:
    Payload - The payload type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Payload>, Sequence<Payload>, IndexedSource<Payload>, Source<Payload>, BidirectionalIterable<Payload>, ProtectedBidirectionalIterable<Payload>, ProtectedIterable<Payload>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractListSequence

    public abstract class AbstractSequence<Payload>
extends AbstractIndexedSource<Payload>
implements Sequence<Payload>
    A AbstractSequence is an abstract base implementation of a Sequence.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Torsten Krause (tk at markenwerk dot net)

      • hashCode

        public final int hashCode()
        Description copied from interface: Sequence
        Returns the hash code of this Sequence.

        The hash code of a Sequence is defined to be the result of the following calculation: 

         int hashCode = 1;
 Iterator<Payload> iterator = sequence.iterator();
 while (iterator.hasNext()) {
        Payload payload = iterator.next();
        hashCode = 31 * hashCode + (null == payload ? 0 : payload.hashCode());
 }
        Specified by:
        hashCode in interface Sequence<Payload>
        Overrides:
        hashCode in class Object
        Returns:
        The hash code of this Sequence.

      • equals

        public final boolean equals(Object object)
        Description copied from interface: Sequence
        Compares the given object with this Sequence for equality.

        Returns true if and only if the given object is also a Sequence, both Sequences have the same size, and all corresponding pairs of elements in the two Sequences are equal.

        Specified by:
        equals in interface Sequence<Payload>
